<!-- ==========================================================
(Password Reset Page)

Description:
Password reset page template.

This view allows users to define a new password after
accessing a secure email link containing an OOB code.

Server Variables:
- oobCode → Secure action code injected from backend.
  Used by frontend logic to validate and complete
  the password reset process.

Responsibilities:
- Render new password form.
- Validate password and confirmation fields.
- Expose OOB code to frontend logic.
- Provide navigation back to login page.
- Support internationalization for dynamic labels and text.

Structure:
- Includes global header and footer partials.
- Organized using BEM naming convention.
- Divided into:
  1. Reset form section
  2. Navigation link section

Client-Side Behavior:
- Form submission triggers password reset logic (password.js).
- Password confirmation validation handled via JavaScript.
- OOB code is read from window.__OOB_CODE__.
- Reset operation completed via Firebase authentication.

Dependencies:
- password.js
- firebase.js
- linkconfirm.js (if shared flow)
- i18n system
- Global bundle.min.js

Security Notes:
- Password fields use type="password".
- Minimum length enforced via HTML attribute.
- OOB code ensures secure, time-limited action.
- No password data is stored or processed directly in this template.
- All verification and update operations handled via Firebase.

========================================================== -->

<%- include('partials/header') %>

<section class="reset">
  <h1 class="reset__title" data-i18n="resetTitle"></h1>

  <form id="reset-form" class="reset__form">
    <label class="reset__form--label" data-i18n="newPassword"></label>
    <input
      id="reset-password"
      class="reset__form--input"
      type="password"
      required
      minlength="6"
    />

    <label class="reset__form--label" data-i18n="confirmPassword"></label>
    <input
      id="reset-password-confirm"
      class="reset__form--input"
      type="password"
      required
      minlength="6"
    />

    <button class="reset__form--submit" type="submit" data-i18n="submitReset"></button>
  </form>

  <div class="reset__links">
    <a href="/login" class="reset__link" data-i18n="backToLogin"></a>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  window.__OOB_CODE__ = "<%= oobCode %>";
  // The frontend script reads this code to complete
  // the secure password reset operation.
</script>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>